Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.65,0:02:31.49,Default,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,Take Chise to the land of dragons?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.76,0:02:34.54,Default,Alien Gremlin,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.54,0:02:42.65,Default,Alien Gremlin,0000,0000,0000,,Lindel-sama heard a rumor that the \NRobin there has trouble using magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.06,0:02:46.25,Default,Alien Gremlin,0000,0000,0000,,So he insists that you make a wand soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.03,0:02:47.72,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,A wand?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.35,0:02:51.91,Default,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,It's a tool for conveying your \Nintentions to the fae.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.29,0:02:56.30,Default,Alien Gremlin,0000,0000,0000,,He would like you to come see him, Robin.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.30,0:02:59.36,Default,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,I've been out all the time lately, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.60,0:03:02.56,Default,Alien Gremlin,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, don't worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.56,0:03:06.24,Default,Alien Gremlin,0000,0000,0000,,He wants the Robin to come alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.54,0:03:07.92,Default,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,Chise? By herself?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.92,0:03:11.78,Default,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,"I want to spend time with my \Ngranddaughter, not with you," he says.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.21,0:03:13.97,Default,Alien Gremlin,0000,0000,0000,,That old bastard...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.97,0:03:14.82,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Granddaughter?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.82,0:03:16.74,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,So Elias is his son?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.27,0:03:20.58,Default,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,It seems he wants to talk about your wand, \Nthough, so I suppose it's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.11,0:03:22.74,Default,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,Take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.55,0:03:27.51,Default,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,Would you rather not?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.80,0:03:30.84,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,No, but by myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.24,0:03:32.55,Default,Dorg,0000,0000,0000,,You have me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.55,0:03:34.42,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.42,0:03:36.22,Default,Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,Are you done talking?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.61,0:03:38.88,Default,Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,You sure haven't changed at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.88,0:03:39.85,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.85,0:03:42.20,Default,Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, have you forgotten me?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.20,0:03:44.17,Default,Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,We talked, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.50,0:03:47.28,Default,Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,You wouldn't fly with me, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.28,0:03:55.34,Default,Alien Gremlin,0000,0000,0000,,Dragons grow up in various ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.67,0:04:00.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to be big enough for you\Nto be able to ride me, so it works out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.39,0:04:02.51,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.11,0:04:15.51,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Silky.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.50,0:04:25.06,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'll see you soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.66,0:04:26.90,Default,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,Take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.37,0:04:28.96,Default,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,It's cold over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.96,0:04:30.44,Default,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,Don't freeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.76,0:04:31.41,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.34,0:04:35.40,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Elias?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.04,0:04:36.88,Default,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.78,0:04:40.58,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,It's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.58,0:04:42.05,Default,Alien Gremlin,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.04,0:04:48.66,Default,Alien Gremlin,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on tight, so you don't fall off!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.61,0:04:59.70,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.70,0:05:01.87,Default,Alien Gremlin,0000,0000,0000,,It's a cloaking spell.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.87,0:05:03.96,Default,Alien Gremlin,0000,0000,0000,,No one will find us now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.96,0:05:07.20,Default,Alien Gremlin,0000,0000,0000,,It's a lot quicker than \Nswimming through the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.20,0:05:08.11,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,The sea?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.50,0:05:09.98,Default,Alien Gremlin,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a selkie.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.50,0:05:16.66,Default,Alien Gremlin,0000,0000,0000,,I'm a citizen of the great seas, \Nwith both a human and seal form.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.09,0:05:58.52,Default,Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.52,0:06:00.92,Default,Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be there as soon as \Nwe get through the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.92,0:06:02.37,Default,Dragon,0000,0000,0000,,Hang on a little longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.00,0:06:03.92,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.70,0:06:21.63,Default,Dorg,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure Elias will be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.95,0:06:22.67,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.47,0:06:34.03,Default,Alien Gremlin,0000,0000,0000,,Lindel-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.43,0:06:38.18,Default,Alien Gremlin,0000,0000,0000,,Lindel-sama, I did what you asked me to.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.18,0:06:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, you did well. Very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.70,0:06:43.46,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Lindel-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.46,0:06:44.61,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.61,0:06:46.07,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Long time no see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.54,0:06:48.84,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,You look quite well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.09,0:06:51.74,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,And you've put on some weight.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.09,0:06:53.08,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Good, good.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.71,0:06:56.26,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad to see you've found a good family.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.30,0:06:59.39,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Lindel-san, where did you get those clothes?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.39,0:07:02.91,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I went shopping in town.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.29,0:07:04.57,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,I'm very handsome, aren't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.55,0:07:07.52,Magus-Internal/narrator,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,He kind of resembles Elias.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.81,0:07:10.99,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, guys, say hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.49,0:07:14.24,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be in your care.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.45,0:07:22.03,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't get to explain last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.84,0:07:27.32,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,The land of dragons was established as \Na nesting ground by the first administrator,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.32,0:07:31.42,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,for the few dragons that remained \Nscattered throughout the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.86,0:07:34.67,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,So you weren't the one who made it, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.06,0:07:38.29,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,I used to be a simple nomad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.63,0:07:43.32,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't even have a name, \Nuntil my master gave me one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.64,0:07:44.93,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,All right, we're here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.00,0:08:07.00,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Nevin's tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.51,0:08:16.85,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be preparing supper.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.85,0:08:17.31,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Chise.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.46,0:08:21.82,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,It's your wand. You've gotta cut it yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.01,0:08:28.23,Default,Dorg,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.80,0:08:30.06,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.27,0:08:38.07,Default,Dorg,0000,0000,0000,,What is wrong with you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.31,0:08:41.49,Default,Dorg,0000,0000,0000,,Who falls without even trying \Nto break their fall?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.49,0:08:42.27,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Ow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.27,0:08:43.07,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.07,0:08:45.05,Default,Alien Gremlin,0000,0000,0000,,You're so overprotective.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.05,0:08:48.80,Default,Alien Gremlin,0000,0000,0000,,It wouldn't kill her to get \Nto know the rocks a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.06,0:08:49.99,Default,Dorg,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.43,0:08:51.93,Default,Dorg,0000,0000,0000,,Should I go?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.93,0:08:54.76,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm going to be the one using it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.29,0:08:57.02,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'll see what I can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.14,0:09:06.87,Default,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Silver.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.35,0:09:11.18,Default,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,Boy, it's quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.61,0:09:16.12,Default,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,Even though that girl is not very talkative.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.69,0:09:20.40,Default,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,The air feels terribly cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.59,0:09:27.29,Magus-Internal/narrator,Phonebird,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, Mr. Ainsworth.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.88,0:09:31.99,Magus-Internal/narrator,Phonebird,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Adolf Stroud. I'm with \Nthe College administration.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.76,0:09:33.79,Default,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,College?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.32,0:09:36.68,Magus-Internal/narrator,Phonebird,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get straight to business.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.18,0:09:43.20,Default,Phonebird,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to speak in depth about \Nthe future of the human child.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.13,0:09:56.94,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Reindeer soup.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.30,0:09:59.11,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,I imagine this is your first time having it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.11,0:09:59.94,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.01,0:10:06.07,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,It's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.55,0:10:09.63,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,You've got scrapes all over.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.63,0:10:10.54,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Let me see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.38,0:10:22.02,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,My hands are what's called healing hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.30,0:10:24.89,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,As long as you aren't mortally \Nwounded, I can heal you on the spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.41,0:10:28.33,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,There used to be more of us, before.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.12,0:10:32.30,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,But not many have been born in \Nthe past few hundred years.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.73,0:10:41.96,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Have long have you been alive, Lindel-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.96,0:10:45.14,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Are other mages long-lived, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.57,0:10:48.99,Default,Alien Gremlin,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's why you were \Nmaking such a fuss earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.99,0:10:51.15,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,That idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.15,0:10:53.37,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,He hasn't explained anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.37,0:10:54.23,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,What does he...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.23,0:10:58.88,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Err, sorry, I should have asked Elias.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.37,0:11:07.21,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Chise, the reason I brought you \Nhere alone is because I'm worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.81,0:11:13.08,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,He seems to want to tame you, \Nas one would a reindeer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.94,0:11:17.85,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,And Chise, you seem to be content with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.56,0:11:30.82,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,The person who gave birth to me \Ntold me that they shouldn't have.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.56,0:11:38.42,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,My mother didn't need me, \Nso she ran away. She died.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.75,0:11:44.22,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I think my brother and father \Nran away from me, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.36,0:11:50.41,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,Elias is the only who's kept me nearby.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.45,0:11:58.24,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I don't ask him \Nanything he doesn't say.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.77,0:12:01.20,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I {\i1}want{\i0} to be complacent.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.14,0:12:07.90,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Though it doesn't appear that way at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.79,0:12:17.71,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell you an interesting bedtime story.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.61,0:12:20.34,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,An interesting story?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.99,0:12:25.43,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose I'll answer your question, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.12,0:12:30.75,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,But, half of it is as punishment for that \Nbastard, for saddening my granddaughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.06,0:12:36.52,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Long ago, when the world was still dark,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.52,0:12:41.07,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,before the power of steam, and before even \Nthe power of the old, earthen oil...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.36,0:12:50.38,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,We mages were all aware that \Nwe were not normal people.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.12,0:12:59.66,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,For we saw magical creatures, and worked \Nmiracles that the ordinary person could not.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.97,0:13:04.07,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,And at times, we lived very long lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.96,0:13:10.51,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know why we're so long-lived, \Nor possess abilities humans do not.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.08,0:13:15.78,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,It may simply be that fate \Nwanted us to be born so.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.70,0:13:20.88,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,But those who were not satisfied \Ncontinued to seek an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.17,0:13:23.44,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,"Why are we so?"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.13,0:13:28.22,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,"Is there a duty that we must fulfill?"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.62,0:13:33.21,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Many of our kind perished in their search.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.26,0:13:45.96,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,I wandered alone, sick of that way of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.76,0:13:51.75,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,One night, there were wolves, and I had \Nno choice but to stand watch all night.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.95,0:13:57.42,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,However, the wolves never came.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.19,0:14:01.85,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Instead, {\i1}it{\i0} came.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.72,0:14:10.09,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,It came as certain as night on two legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.87,0:14:18.91,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.41,0:14:26.04,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.69,0:14:30.01,Magus-Flashback,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,I'm hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.59,0:14:33.04,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.45,0:14:48.11,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,You're awake, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.64,0:14:51.94,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,You were asleep all night.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.94,0:14:55.17,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,You're so huge, it was a pain to carry you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.40,0:14:59.61,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you going to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.70,0:15:03.16,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.51,0:15:04.65,Magus-Flashback,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.50,0:15:09.89,Magus-Flashback,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,When I came to, I was in \Nthe forest, and I was walking.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.34,0:15:16.19,Magus-Flashback,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,Avoiding people, I walked, walked, \Nand walked, until I was here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.77,0:15:18.64,Magus-Flashback,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,I'm tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.57,0:15:25.60,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.14,0:15:27.26,Magus-Flashback,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.99,0:15:33.39,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,You look to be an apparition of some kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.39,0:15:36.58,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,But you wear flesh, like a living creature.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.92,0:15:38.59,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,What are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.17,0:15:40.16,Magus-Flashback,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.61,0:15:46.50,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's go see my master.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.09,0:15:49.87,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,She's a strange one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.16,0:15:54.59,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,She may be at the other side of \Nthe world. She may be right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.59,0:15:58.44,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,She may be alive a hundred years \Nfrom now or a hundred years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.80,0:16:02.56,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Being a meddler, she may provide guidance.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.72,0:16:07.77,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,I'd imagine it would be less painful than \Naimlessly wandering through the wilds.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.25,0:16:09.95,Magus-Flashback,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.95,0:16:11.35,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Lindel.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.96,0:16:16.38,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,The ordinary people call us "mages."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.49,0:16:21.77,Magus-Flashback,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.46,0:16:25.43,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,An ancient technique for finding the missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.71,0:16:29.23,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Gather some spruce, tie it in \Nred string, and set it loose.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.51,0:16:32.48,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,The spruce covering the ground is \Nthe dining table of the forest god.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.48,0:16:35.23,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,We ask for their help and for directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.19,0:16:42.63,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,My guide, take us past the \Nfog, to the one we seek.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.14,0:16:55.72,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,The fog is thickening.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.72,0:16:56.69,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Stay with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.20,0:17:24.12,Magus-Flashback,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,Water.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.12,0:17:25.23,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,The sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.23,0:17:26.38,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Have a taste.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.38,0:17:27.66,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,It's fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.19,0:17:38.19,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,That's my master's home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.01,0:17:50.99,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.99,0:17:51.98,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Rahab.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.98,0:17:52.54,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Are you home?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.54,0:17:57.76,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,Is that Lindel?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.01,0:18:02.08,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see your face here often.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.49,0:18:04.51,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,A pity, since your name's derived\Nfrom that of the tree of gatherings.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.51,0:18:06.98,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,That name was your choice, Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.98,0:18:10.40,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,You need to make an effort to \Ninteract with people more—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.40,0:18:10.91,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.91,0:18:12.95,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,I found him yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.27,0:18:15.73,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted you to take a look at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.06,0:18:19.39,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.39,0:18:22.97,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,Though then again, you're pretty big.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.32,0:18:24.74,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,Can you become smaller?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.04,0:18:26.35,Magus-Flashback,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,Smaller?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.35,0:18:27.37,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.37,0:18:28.77,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,About human size.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.77,0:18:30.08,Magus-Flashback,Elias,0000,0000,0000,,Human...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.41,0:18:35.30,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,Like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.30,0:18:36.37,Magus-Flashback,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.37,0:18:37.50,Magus-Flashback,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,Well done.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.10,0:18:38.95,Magus-Flashback,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,Come.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.41,0:18:47.89,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.89,0:18:49.43,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.43,0:18:55.19,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,He's as close to a spirit or fairy as you\Ncan get, but there's a hint of human in him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.58,0:18:59.38,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,It would make sense if he were \Nsimply a human who'd gotten
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.38,0:19:02.38,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,himself transformed trying \Nto use black magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.80,0:19:04.45,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,But this seems more like...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.99,0:19:11.04,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember anything about what \Nhappened before you started walking?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.70,0:19:14.54,Magus-Flashback,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,Anything I remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.52,0:19:19.42,Magus-Flashback,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,Red.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.76,0:19:20.62,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Red?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.51,0:19:25.01,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to force \Nyourself to remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.90,0:19:30.68,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,Lindel, you'll take care of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.68,0:19:31.53,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.53,0:19:32.81,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Why me?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.81,0:19:34.81,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,You've already taken pity on him once.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.81,0:19:37.08,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,You ought to take care of \Nhim until he's independent.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.59,0:19:40.27,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,I have to follow the reindeer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.27,0:19:43.56,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,It's about time you took an apprentice.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.56,0:19:46.61,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,We ought not to live by ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.61,0:19:47.78,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,Remember what I taught you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.67,0:19:51.79,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,I won't tell you to love your enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.13,0:19:55.91,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,But the neighbors love us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.62,0:20:00.67,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,We lend a staff to those \Nwho have lost their way.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.58,0:20:05.51,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,It's not as if we asked to be loved.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.79,0:20:07.56,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Not me nor you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.80,0:20:09.61,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,We might as well be cursed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.41,0:20:14.52,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,Curses and blessings are \Nthe same in essence, Lindel.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.83,0:20:16.49,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,What matters is how you take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.35,0:20:20.42,Magus-Flashback,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.42,0:20:21.85,Magus-Flashback,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.14,0:20:26.21,Magus-Flashback,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,If you'd rather not have me \Nhere, I'll continue walking.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.29,0:20:28.55,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,To where?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.92,0:20:32.78,Magus-Flashback,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know, but you're busy, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.59,0:20:36.01,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,I don't take apprentices.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.54,0:20:44.86,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,So from now on, you're my acquaintance.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.70,0:20:50.68,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,I would surely have to provide a weary\N acquaintance a place to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.47,0:20:52.98,Magus-Flashback,Edeglord,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not in need.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.98,0:20:55.07,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,You're one to talk. You collapsed!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.07,0:20:57.01,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my, how kind of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.01,0:20:57.74,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.74,0:21:00.73,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,Now that that's settled, we're friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.12,0:21:02.66,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.24,0:21:04.76,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,I'm guessing you don't have one.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.76,0:21:05.92,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,What should we call you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.92,0:21:09.07,Magus-Flashback,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go again, with Master's \Nname-giving obsession.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.95,0:21:14.07,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,The gods and the fairies are all with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.07,0:21:17.13,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,Even if no one takes notice of you,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.92,0:21:24.61,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,even if you're sad, suffering, and crushed by \Nloneliness, they will always watch over you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.48,0:21:29.67,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,So take comfort, and save yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.91,0:21:53.30,Magus-Flashback,Doctor Who,0000,0000,0000,,Elias.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.86,0:22:00.51,Magus-Internal/narrator,Phonebird,0000,0000,0000,,Hello? Ainsworth?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.74,0:22:02.89,Magus-Internal/narrator,Phonebird,0000,0000,0000,,Senpai! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.89,0:22:03.96,Default,Grandpa,0000,0000,0000,,Renfred.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.61,0:22:09.00,Magus-Internal/narrator,Phonebird,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to ruin her if you continue to \Ndo nothing more than let her live with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.72,0:23:57.86,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,The story of the mage's past.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.86,0:24:01.77,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,The girl is shaken by the \Ntruth that had been hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.77,0:24:04.96,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,What does the brief parting \Nbring to the two?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.45,0:24:09.15,Default,Chise,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell you what I haven't \Nbeen able to tell you, too.
